	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, I sorta knew I'd come across this. I have been in a group that says you loot what you kill... I have been in groups that say casters don't get to loot, and then those who just don't let clerics loot. Of course I have been leader a couple times and have had to repeat ALPHA LOOT like 50 times... it can be frustrating to be leader. But sometimes you just cannot afford to boot someone without really trying.<br><br>Also, it sucks that we are generally the poorest class. I have heard that the higher lvl buffs and such reaquire items that can become costly. Someone told me one of his buffs can cost him up to 285pp for one casting! How could that be?? How could anyone afford that? I suppose higher lvl clerics can rez for donations... but if I can never loot that is going to be a problem.<br><br>I just wish other classes would have respect for us. If we run oom and cannot heal, they get mad and notice how we STOPPED healing. But when we are keeping their butts alive, they don't give it a second thought. Ridiculous. I know I will always be considerate of clerics when playing my druid. I have so much empathy for them now. <br><br>I said my piece... peace!<br><br>Orchyd<br>8th Gnome Cleric<br>(Ittie Bittie Brigade)<br>Brell Serilis<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
