	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings everyone MJ from seventh hammer here. <br><br>Just wanted to drop my 2 cents in on the loot subject. I used to have the same problem, never getting any loot. Then I decided one thing a group is only as good as its leadership... Yah so you cant always find a good group. solution: you be the leader.<br><br>My rules for a group are as follows. <br>#1. %t pulls this means YOU dont.<br>#2. I loot/sell/split. trust me its better.<br>#3. I'm a $%#@^ about my rules. but I run a good group.<br>#4. Dont run unless I say. But do run when I say.<br>#5. If your healing call your heals during battle.<br><br>now the thing is if your in an area where you have to wait on a list to get in any group. just wait, sit and heal and sit and heal and NEVER loot when your not the leader ppl tend to respect dedication to the job, and when you are leading... then you can make the rules.<br><br>Anywho its been a week since I've started using these, and yes I've had to boot ppl for looting. And yes ppl have quite before even trying the rules out. but I promise you when that first split comes... and everyone gets 20 or 30 plat. They will love you. <br><br>I've been in High Hold Keep only a week, gone up 7 levels, banked over 2k plat and now when I login and /ooc RR group forming up at the bank. I have ppl leaving thier other groups to come and join mine. <br><br>The only other thing I can say... is a camp goes bad and someone is gonna die... tell your group to run and take the hit for them. It inspires loyalty in the group and build your reputation as a good leader. <br>Good luck all and happy hunting. =)<br>~~MJ 27 cleric &lt;Maidens of Norrath&gt;<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
