	   <tr><td colspan=2>Man... I'm glad to hear that someone else is having this problem.&nbsp;&nbsp;Just today we we're camping the Throne Room at Crushbone.  I was doing the usual buff, heal, med, med, med, twiddle thumbs, heal, buff, med... etc.  We brought down Emp. Crush and he droped the DRT.  Immediately the group (as usual) started talking about the loot like I wasn't even there.  Nevermind I was the one who Smited Emp Crush to half his life bar and used the rest of my mana for healing.  When I asked them for a /random to determine who got the loot, they laughed.  Needless to say, I made up my mind to leave, and waited till the next spawn.  I jumped out the castle window and left them to their fate.  Lesson: Don't get chincy on your cleric and never, I repeat, NEVER laugh at them when the issue of loot comes up.  You may find them leaving you at the most inconvienent time.  I pride myself on helping others in need (usually for free when soloing even) but I don't stand for those full of greed.<br><br>Dindack<br>Cleric of Brell<br>17 Seasons<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
