	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello fellow clerics,<br><br>I am a 100% pure character.&nbsp;&nbsp;Never had a higher level character besides this one, and, to be frank, clerics are the poorest class in the game.<br><br>I was wearing a BRONZE(yes bronze) BP at level 35.<br><br>I had 130 Wisdom at level 30.<br><br>I am now level 37, with 169 wisdom and 1kpp.  How. do you ask?<br>As soon as you hit 30th, go to Rathe Mts.  Get a grp and hunt Hill Giants, the loot is insane and the exp is decent.  Also, go to Iceclad and kill some cougars for a few days - WIN THOSE CC EARRINGS - good sell and trade item. I found that by doing this I was able to Aquire the following nice new items since 30th level :<br>Foreman's Tunic (GAWD so glad to get rid of the GD bronze)3 Wis<br>Two Velium Jasper rings - 7 wis each =D<br>Boots of the Reliant<br>Cleric quest guantlets<br>Kunzar Cloak<br>CBB for wrist slot - 5 wis, (camp the Great Owamp)<br>Paw of Opolla - 9 wis/agi 5 sta 5 mana<br>CGS - offhand 9 wis (forget your weapon just leave one in your inventory at this stage.)<br>And some others, cant remember them all<br><br>I started with 105, yes 105 wis.<br>You will be poor, but it does get better at these levels, beggars must realize also that altho we make more money at the higher levels, there are more expensive things we have to buy.<br><br>Good luck and stick with it, clerics may not be the best class, but theres no feeling like being the only cleric in L Guk And shouting LFG<br>Teehee<br><br>Darmani Lifebringer<br>37 and climbing Dwarven cleric<br>Povar<br>&lt;Sanguin Choas&gt;  &lt;----- Luv my guild like family ) <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
